<plot>One of three films made in the six-announced "Morton of the Mounted" series: Sergeant Bruce Morton, in charge of the Three Rivers Post of the Royal Northwest Mounted Police is informed by White Feather, an Indian fur-trapper, that for many months, most of the local fur trappers have been systematically robbed, but refuses to name the robbers, fearing for his life. Morton, his horse Dynamite, his dog Captain, and a RCMP corporal, Jimmy Downs, set out to apprehend the culprits. After rescuing Yvonne Travis from the treacherous waters of Horse Shoe Rapids, Morton learns that her father is a fur trader indebted to Mordant, who runs the trading post, and Mordant is using her father's debt to force Yvonne to marry him. Morton decides that Mordant could bear watching, but Mordant has already decided that Morton is bad news for his operation, and he sends his henchman out to get rid of Morton and Downs.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?117021</url></doc>
